      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAPPER THIRTYNINE (1) has a big weight to carry here, but he has the 62kg for a reason and it can be considered a positive that the stable has elected not to claim. Has been freshened since the most recent start, with a soft Flemington jumpout in between, and while it's been over a year between wins, most races he's contested have been of higher quality than this. QUICKAZ (9) is the most intriguing runner in the race, stepping up from 3YO fillies grade last prep, but the fourth placing to Point Barrow looks good form for this and she gets weight off all rivals. YAMASHITA'S GOLD (8) returned to winning form last start and he's drawn to go on with it. LIM'S BIGHORN (3) is yet to find his best this prep but will be at peak fitness now and is better suited back to 1200m.",
